.TH LIVE-SETUP 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
live-setup \- perform first-boot setup tasks in a live system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B live-setup
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B live-setup
is a small boot-time helper used by the live system.
It performs the initial setup tasks that make a live session behave like a
normal desktop while preserving the live environment.

The script exits immediately if it is not running on a live system.
When it does run, it restores disabled live services, performs USB-related live
setup, copies a machine ID if needed, sets the paper size from the locale, makes
sure the APT partial directory exists, and adjusts the console/session flow for
non-systemd boots.

This script is normally invoked automatically from the live setup integration,
not started by hand.
.SH OPTIONS
.B live-setup
accepts no script-specific options.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /live/etc/init.d/live-restore-services
Helper used to restore live services.
.TP
.I /live/etc/init.d/live-usb-save
Helper used for USB-specific live setup.
.TP
.I /etc/machine-id
Created from the dbus machine-id when missing.
.TP
.I /etc/papersize
Paper size written according to the current locale.
.TP
.I /etc/default/locale
Locale source used to determine paper size.
.TP
.I /var/cache/apt/archives/partial
APT partial directory created if missing.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR live-setup.service (8),
.BR init.d/live-setup (8)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
